<subSubSection id="C339651529621961FF75448C0BD2B55C" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B9C369E29621961FF75448C0BD2B55C" blockId="2.[151,1436,706,892]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis id="B957EA8C29621961FF75448C0900B524" bold="true" box="[198,326,746,772]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new genus has a carapace similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C234D1D29621961FC96448C0BFEB523" box="[805,952,746,771]" class="Malacostraca" family="Leuconidae" genus="Bytholeucon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B957EA8C29621961FC96448C0BFEB523" box="[805,952,746,771]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Bytholeucon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a single pair of pleopods in males and is unique in the family 
<taxonomicName id="4C234D1D29621961FE3845740A52B50C" box="[395,532,786,812]" class="Malacostraca" family="Leuconidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Leuconidae</taxonomicName>
by possession of penial lobes between the fifth pereiopods. 
<emphasis id="B957EA8C29621961FF75455C0915B574" bold="true" box="[198,339,826,852]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Etymology.</emphasis>
The genus name derives from phallus (gr.: penis) and - 
<taxonomicName id="4C234D1D29621961FC53455C0C76B574" box="[992,1072,826,852]" class="Malacostraca" family="Leuconidae" genus="Leucon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="2" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">leucon</taxonomicName>
(the family name); the species is named after the position of the 
<typeStatus id="5498883C29621961FD9345040A15B55C" box="[544,595,866,892]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">type</typeStatus>
locality, the abyssal plains.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
